Test Plan Template (Manual QA â€“ E-commerce Demo)
1. Objective

The purpose of this test plan is to validate the core functionality, usability, and reliability of the e-commerce web application.
The goal is to identify defects that may affect user experience, checkout flow, and data integrity.

2. Scope
In Scope

User Registration

User Login / Logout

Product Search

Product Details Page

Add to Cart

Update Cart

Checkout Process

Form Validations

Basic UI validation

Out of Scope

Performance testing

Security testing

Payment gateway real transactions

Mobile app testing (if only web)

3. Test Strategy

The following testing approaches will be used:

Functional Testing

Verification of all main business flows and system behavior.

Negative Testing

Validation of invalid inputs and unexpected user actions.

Boundary Value Testing

Testing input limits (e.g., minimum/maximum characters).

Exploratory Testing

Session-based exploration to identify edge cases and usability issues.

4. Test Environment

Browser: Chrome (latest version)

OS: Windows 10

Resolution: 1920x1080

Test Data: Demo user accounts

5. Risk Analysis
Risk	Impact	Mitigation
Checkout failure	High	Detailed test cases for checkout
Form validation issues	Medium	Negative & boundary tests
Session expiration bugs	Medium	Session testing scenarios
6. Entry Criteria

Application is deployed

Test environment accessible

Requirements are available

7. Exit Criteria

All high severity defects addressed

All planned test cases executed

Test summary report completed

8. Deliverables

Test Plan

Test Cases

Bug Reports

Traceability Matrix

Test Summary Report

9. Assumptions

Application is intended for desktop users

All prices are fixed and not dynamically updated

No real payment processing occurs in demo version
